<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Contact StoryLoom</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
</head>
<body>

    {{> header}}

    <main class="container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h1>Contact Us</h1>
            
            <h2>Email</h2>
            <p>The best way to get in touch is by email.</p>
            
            <h3>Before You Write</h3>
            <ul class="dashed-list">
                <li>Include a descriptive subject line, or your email may end up in a spam folder.</li>
                <li>Don't send email as HTML only, or only within attachments.</li>
                <li>Be patient. As this is an undergraduate project, inquiries usually get a response within a few days.</li>
                <li>The email addresses below are not clickable — please type them manually. This helps avoid spam bots.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Contact Information</h3>
            <div class="contact-block">
                <p><strong>1. General Inquiries & Project Feedback</strong></p>
                <p style="margin-top: 5px; color: #005599; font-weight: bold;">thaitq.23bi14396 (at) your-domain</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 5px;">For general information about the StoryLoom undergraduate project, bug reports, or catalog errors.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="contact-block">
                <p><strong>2. Phone Contact</strong></p>
                <p style="margin-top: 5px; color: #005599; font-weight: bold;">0934661719</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 5px;">Direct line for urgent inquiries regarding the archive infrastructure.</p>
            </div>
            
            <h2>Distributed Proofreaders</h2>
            <p>The <a href="#">Distributed Proofreaders</a> site includes active forums, FAQs and other items of interest for text lovers and creators. Contact information is available at the site, and online forums are also used for discussions and collaborative efforts.</p>
            
            <h2>Further Contacts</h2>
            <p>There is an occasional email newsletter and a discussion list for volunteers. Archives of the lists are available as well.</p>
            <ul class="dashed-list">
                <li><a href="#">Mailing lists</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">How to subscribe to mailing lists</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </main>

    {{> footer}}

</body>
</html>